trans-unit.source: The SYSXPLAIN_STATEMENT_TIMINGS table captures information about statement timings which occurred during statements that were executed using RUNTIMESTATISTICS with XPLAIN style.

seg-source.mrk: The SYSXPLAIN_STATEMENT_TIMINGS table captures information about statement timings which occurred during statements that were executed using RUNTIMESTATISTICS with XPLAIN style.

target.mrk: The SYSXPLAIN_STATEMENT_TIMINGS table captures information about statement timings which occurred during statements that were executed using RUNTIMESTATISTICS with XPLAIN style.

trans-unit.source: See "Working with RunTimeStatistics" in <ph conref="../conrefs.dita#pub/cittuning"></ph> for information on how to configure this. Note in particular that you must call SYSCS_UTIL.SYSCS_SET_STATISTICS_TIMING(1) to enable timing information to be captured. trans-unit.source: select s.stmt_text, st.execute_time from my_stats.sysxplain_statements s, my_stats.sysxplain_statement_timings st where s.timing_id = st.timing_id order by st.execute_time desc
